					";s:11:"author_name";s:15:"Kevin Kniestedt";s:5:"title";s:49:"KPLU School of Jazz Volume 9 to be released May 7";s:4:"link";s:73:"http://groovenotes.org/kplu-school-of-jazz-volume-9-to-be-released-may-7/";s:2:"id";s:30:"http://groovenotes.org/?p=4892";s:7:"updated";s:20:"2013-05-04T17:34:17Z";s:9:"published";s:20:"2013-05-04T17:34:03Z";s:7:"summary";s:345:"KPLU?s new School Of Jazz CD &#8211; Volume 9 will be released this coming Tuesday, May 7. Listeners can purchase the CD at kplu.org. All proceeds go to the schools? music programs. KPLU has raised over $70,000 for the schools, since the project started. This year, bands from Ballard High School (Seattle), Graham-Kapowsin High School [&#8230;]";s:12:"atom_content";s:1781:"<p>KPLU?s new School Of Jazz CD &#8211; Volume 9 will be released this coming Tuesday, May 7. Listeners can purchase the CD at kplu.org. All proceeds go to the schools? music programs. KPLU has raised over $70,000 for the schools, since the project started. This year, bands from Ballard High School (Seattle), Graham-Kapowsin High School (Graham), Jackson High School (Mill Creek), Lakewood Jazz Choir (Arlington), Lynnwood High School (Bothell), Mercer Island High School, Mountlake Terrace High School, Newport High School (Bellevue), Roosevelt High School (Seattle), Seattle JazzED, South Whidbey High School, and W.F. West High School (Chehalis) will be featured on the CD. This year?s professional jazz mentors include Thomas Marriott, Tracy Knoop, Greta Matassa, Brad Boal, Jay Thomas, Travis Ranney, Dan Wager, Steve Treseler, Neil Welch and Andy Omdahl.</p>
<p>The School of Jazz project has won has won two national awards for its effort. On May 7th during KPLU?s Midday Jazz, KPLU will broadcast the entire CD (one song every 30-minutes) between 9am ? 3pm PST. Listeners can hear it locally in the Seattle/Tacoma market on 88.5 FM, or online at kplu.org.</p>
